  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nOpenEthereum is approaching the end of its support, and node operators are being encouraged to use Erigon instead.\r\n\r\nOne great thing about OpenEthereum was the presence of [official Docker images](https://hub.docker.com/r/openethereum/openethereum) for each release. This has made it very easy for users to ensure they are always running an up-to-date node.\r\n\r\nErigon, on the other hand, does not appear to have any official Docker images. This forces node operators to build images for each release they wish to use, or to evaluate unofficial third-party options which may be outdated, poorly supported, malicious, or otherwise problematic. This point of additional friction presents a barrier-to-entry for new Erigon users, who may settle for the current majority client Geth, or worse, not run a node at all.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nThe OpenEthereum team did a great job of pushing each release to Docker Hub with a new tag. The exact same setup would be excellent to have for Erigon as well.",
